# Always-On Rules

This file loads on EVERY request, regardless of what file you're editing. Keep it minimal -- only rules that apply everywhere.

- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`, no `@ts-ignore`, no `enum` (use `as const`).
- Named exports only. No default exports.
- Run `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint` before committing.
- One logical change per commit.
